<div class="description">
    <h3>Description</h3>

    <div class="body">
        <p>I wanted to get all the terms from parsed user's query - so I used the getQueryTerms().</p>

<p>But as it works well with english words it has problems with other languages with national characters.</p>

<p>Eg. we have the word 'żółw' (turtle). The function returns two terms: 'z' and 'olw'.
Or 'naleśnik' (pancake) - we get 'nale' and 'snik'.</p>

<p>The words are being split on those characters. I've tried setting and forcing utf-8 wherever possible (functions, static variables and locale) on Linux and Windows, ZF 1.7.0.</p>

<p>Is this a bug or a feature?</p>

